index.html.description:
Have no idea how to navigate or use this vault? Click this link to start with the RARE Vault Manual Help Guide
2025-08-31
#⚠️-attention are out of the daily record sheets for the binder.  Sonja - I have printed off more binder sheets and will take to the barn this week.
#⚠️-attention I brought out more poop bags. In the grey cabinet by the steps, on the bottom shelf is a bucket with Walmart grocery bags. No notices with this tag in the last week.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Restart vitahawk 9/1
#🦅🩺-bird-care/long-term Isn't perching but is standing. Possibly soft tissue injury? #🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Monday crew please double check the legs
#🦅🩺-bird-care/long-term Did not see any injury, but has a limp. Was standing on one leg. Sunday crew: could you double check that you can’t appreciate any injuries either?
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term The finder had mentioned that he thought the bird had a leg injury. We couldn’t appreciate anything, but the legs were stiff. Could you please double check when you take out of cage on Sunday?
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Green pellet
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Rewrapped in fig 8 body wrap.  Recheck on 9/11
#🦅🩺-bird-care/long-term The Ulna is starting to form a nice callus, I think when I originally wrapped the bones were not kept immobile and the healing was delayed. .
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Last day for TAB
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Metacam - 1.1mL due to the xarays and the extension on the wing.  Please refer to PT schedule.  Wrap will come off on 9/11..
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Recheck wrap on 9/4.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Lets take a break on the Vitahawk.  Restart on 9/1/25
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Lets take a break on the Vitahawk.  Restart on 9/1/25
#🦅🩺-bird-care/long-term Xrays showed L fx of the carpometacarpus (hand).
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Last day for meds and fluids
#🦅🩺-bird-care/long-term Could not appreciate any differences between the L & R metacarpals.  No bruising, removed wrap.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Sonja, please check the wings. Thank you.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/long-term Wondering about this bird’s vision:  Turned head to look at me with far eye.  Tilted head noticeably when looking at me.  Flew close to me once, & then actually brushed against me in flight.  Wonder if its depth perception isn’t good.  Could it be partially blind?
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Likely ready to start PT in the next week or so.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Re-check 8/28.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Do Dex IM tomorrow.
#🦅🩺-bird-care/short-term Please document if eating.

info_showOrphanNodes.description: Show nodes that are not connected to any other nodes.

info_showAttachments.description: Show attachments like images and PDFs as nodes in the graph.

info_allowGlobalGraph.description: Allow the user to view the global graph of all nodes.

info_allowExpand.description: Allow the user to pop-out the graph view to take up the whole screen

info_attractionForce.description: How much should linked nodes attract each other? This will make the graph appear more clustered.

info_linkLength.description: How long should the links between nodes be? The shorter the links the more connected nodes will cluster together.

info_repulsionForce.description: How much should nodes repel each other? This will make disconnected parts more spread out.

info_centralForce.description: How much should nodes be attracted to the center? This will make the graph appear more dense and circular.

info_edgePruning.description: Edges with a length above this threshold will not be rendered, however they will still contribute to the simulation. This can help large tangled graphs look more organised. Hovering over a node will still display these links.

info_minNodeRadius.description: How small should the smallest nodes be? The smaller a node is the less it will attract other nodes.

info_maxNodeRadius.description: How large should the largest nodes be? Nodes are sized by how many links they have. The larger a node is the more it will attract other nodes. This can be used to create a good grouping around the most important nodes.

info_allowResizing.description: Whether or not to allow the sidebars to be resized

info_allowCollapsing.description: Whether or not to allow the sidebars to be collapsed

info_rightDefaultWidth.description: The default width of the right sidebar

info_leftDefaultWidth.description: The default width of the left sidebar
